6.4 Save Modal (reusable component)
A bottom sheet (mobile) or centered modal (desktop). Used by all integration points.

HEADER: “Save to Field Notes”
FORM FIELDS:
• Title: text input. Pre-filled from source (Deep Scan signal title, creator video place name, imported page title). Editable.
• Category: dropdown. Values: Food, Event, Nature, Culture, Nightlife, Transit, Lodging, Activity, Practical, Other. Pre-suggested based on source when possible.
• Region: text input. Pre-filled from source location when available.
• Country: text input or country dropdown. Pre-filled when available.
• Seasonality: optional dropdown. Year-round, Spring, Summer, Autumn, Winter, Specific dates. If specific dates selected: two date pickers appear.
• Notes: optional textarea for personal context.
BUTTONS:
• “Save” → POST /api/field-notes with form data + source_type + source_reference_id. Close modal. Toast: “Saved to Field Notes.”
• “Cancel” → close modal, discard form.
VALIDATION: title is required. Category is required. Everything else optional.
6.5 Import Modal
A bottom sheet (mobile) or centered modal (desktop). Opened from the library’s “Import URL” button.

HEADER: “Import from URL”
STEP 1: URL input + “Fetch details” button. Loading spinner while fetching.
STEP 2 (on success): Preview card showing: extracted title, description snippet, thumbnail (if og:image), suggested category, suggested region. All fields editable by the traveler.
• “Save” → POST /api/field-notes with source_type = ‘user_import’, source_url = the URL, and confirmed/edited metadata.
• “Cancel” → close.
ERROR STATES:
• Invalid URL: “Please enter a valid URL.”
• Fetch failed: “Couldn’t read that page. You can still save it as a manual note.” with “Save as manual note” button that opens Save Modal with the URL in the description.
• Rate limit: “Too many imports. Try again in a minute.”
6.6 FOCL Field Notes Management (/focl/field-notes)
Founder-only page showing platform-wide Field Notes metrics:
• Total notes across all accounts
• Notes by source type breakdown (pie chart or stat cards)
• Most-saved destinations (top 10 country/region pairs)
• Notes with sensitivity flags (list for review — founder can view but not edit traveler notes)
• Feature activation status card (from feature_registry) with activation/deactivation toggle
7. API Routes
Route	Method	Purpose + Returns
/api/field-notes	GET	List notes. Params: ?status=active, ?country_code=, ?category=, ?trip_id=. Returns { notes[], count }.
/api/field-notes	POST	Create note. Body: title, category + optional fields. Emits field_note_created. Returns { note }.
/api/field-notes/[note_id]	PATCH	Update note. Body: any editable field. Emits field_note_attached_to_trip if trip changed. Returns { note }.
/api/field-notes/[note_id]	DELETE	Delete note (permanent). Emits field_note_deleted. Returns { success }.
/api/field-notes/[note_id]/convert-to-activity	POST	Convert to activity_candidate. Requires attached_trip_id. Creates activity row, sets note status. Emits field_note_converted_to_activity.
/api/field-notes/import	POST	Import URL metadata. Body: { url }. Fetches Open Graph tags server-side. Returns { suggested: { title, description, category?, region? } }. Does NOT create the note.
8. FOCL Registration
Feature ID: F-6.7.2. Display name: Field Notes (Saved Intelligence). Phase: 2. Default enabled: false. Minimum mode: NORMAL.
Depends on: F-6.5.13 (Deep Scan) and F-6.6.11 (Creator Discovery) — soft dependencies. Field Notes works without them but is richer with them. If neither is active, the only source types available are user_import, voice_capture, and manual_note.
When F-6.7.2 is inactive: Save buttons do not appear on Deep Scan or Creator Discovery. Account page does not show Field Notes row. /account/field-notes shows “Field Notes is coming soon.”
9. Governance Events
field_note_created — { note_id, source_type, country_code, category, account_id }
field_note_attached_to_trip — { note_id, trip_id, previous_trip_id (if moved), account_id }
field_note_converted_to_activity — { note_id, activity_candidate_id, trip_id, account_id }
field_note_archived — { note_id, account_id }
field_note_deleted — { note_id, account_id }
10. Stress Behavior (§15.0)
Under PROTECTIVE mode: Field Notes remain readable. Save actions may be queued but not blocked. Import normalizer may degrade to title-only extraction (skip Open Graph fetch if external network is slow). No Field Notes are lost under any stress condition.
Load test scenario: 200+ Field Notes per account, clustered across 5+ regions. Verify library pagination performance, filter responsiveness, and Trip Spark clustering speed.
11. Test Obligations
E2E tests (tests/e2e/field-notes.spec.ts):
• Create note from manual entry → appears in library
• Create note from import URL (mock response) → preview renders → save → appears in library
• View detail page → all fields display correctly
• Attach to trip → trip badge appears on library card
• Convert to activity → status changes to converted_to_activity, activity_candidate created
• Archive → note disappears from active list, appears under archived filter
• Delete → confirmation dialog → note removed permanently
Contract tests:
• RLS: create note as user A, attempt read as user B → 0 results
• Feature gate: verify save buttons hidden when F-6.7.2 is disabled
Stress tests:
• 200+ notes per account → library loads within 2 seconds
• Cluster detection with 50 notes across 8 regions → Trip Spark banner appears correctly
12. §9a Dependency Declaration
• Trip workspace: YES — save discovery shortcut in workspace strip. Risk: if Field Notes API fails, hide the card gracefully (don’t error the workspace).
• Readiness: NO
• Right Now / context: NO
• FOCL / activation: YES — new FOCL page, feature_registry entry. Risk: if feature is off, FOCL page shows “Not yet activated” with prerequisites.


